(B) Feature Engineering¶¶

In [13]:
# Convert Gender into 1 or 0 
df['Gender'] = df['Gender'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == 'Male' else 0)

# Convert Pre-morbid ADL into 1 or 0 
df['Pre-morbid ADL'] = df['Pre-morbid ADL'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == 'I' else 0)

# Convert interface into 1 or 0
df['Interface'] = df['Interface'].replace({"Nasal":1,"N/A":0})

# Convert Oxygen delivery service into five levels
df['Oxygen delivery device, first in ICU']= df['Oxygen delivery device, first in ICU'].replace({'NC':1,'VM':2,
                                                                                                                                                                                            'NRM':3,"HFNC":4,                                                                                           'NIV':5})
# Convert strings with N/Y into 0 and 1
df=df.replace({'Y':1, "N":0})

# Replace NA valus of HFNC
df["HFNC, FiO2"].fillna(df["HFNC, FiO2"].mean(),inplace=True)
df["HFNC, flow"].fillna(df["HFNC, flow"].mean(),inplace=True)

# Set target and features
feature_set = df.drop(['Intubation in first 24 hours'], axis = 1)
target_set = df[['Intubation in first 24 hours']]

# Train Test Split
test_size = 0.4
random_state = 2022
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(feature_set, target_set, \
                                                        test_size= test_size, random_state = random_state)
# Apply MinMaxScaler on Training Set and Testing Set
cols_scale = df.select_dtypes(include=['float64'])

for col in cols_scale:
    
    sc = MinMaxScaler()
    sc.fit(X_train[[col]])
    X_train[col] = sc.transform(X_train[[col]])
    X_test[col] = sc.transform(X_test[[col]])

#Non string columns
non_str_cols = [col for col, dtype in zip(X_train.columns, X_train.dtypes) if dtype != 'object']
X_train_non = X_train[non_str_cols]

    print(col, retain)

(C) Model Fitting¶

Evaluation¶

  1. Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F-Score -> choose the best model (based on test set)
  2. Tune the Hyper-parameters using cross-validation set
  3. See if the accuracy or f-score improve

Supervised Approach¶

  • Benchmark model:
  1. Logistic Regression
  2. KNN
  3. DecisionClassifier
  • Tree based:
  1. Random Forest
  2. XGBoost Ref. https://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/stable/index.html
  3. LightGBM Ref. https://lightgbm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html
  • Naive Bayes Classifier

# Replace NA valus of HFNC
df["HFNC, FiO2"].fillna(df["HFNC, FiO2"].mean(),inplace=True)
df["HFNC, flow"].fillna(df["HFNC, flow"].mean(),inplace=True)

# Set target and features
feature_set = df.drop(['Intubation in first 24 hours'], axis = 1)
feature_set = feature_set.loc[:,[i for i in feature_set.columns if 'ICU' not in i]]
feature_set = feature_set.loc[:,[i for i in feature_set.columns if 'Discharge' not in i]]
target_set = df[['Intubation in first 24 hours']]

# Train Test Split
test_size = 0.4
random_state = 2022



X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(feature_set, target_set,                                                         test_size= test_size, random_state = random_state)
# Apply MinMaxScaler on Training Set and Testing Set
cols_scale = feature_set.select_dtypes(include=['float64'])

for col in cols_scale:
    
    sc = MinMaxScaler()
    sc.fit(X_train[[col]])
    X_train[col] = sc.transform(X_train[[col]])
    X_test[col] = sc.transform(X_test[[col]])



print('Random Forest')

import warnings

print('Testing Accuracy Score: ', rf.score(X_test, y_test).round(4))


# sorted(zip(clf.feature_importances_, X.columns), reverse=True)

plt.show()

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor

# training the trees in our random forest algorithm
train_rf_scores = []
test_rf_scores = []
for depth in range(1, 10):
    rf_boston = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, max_depth=depth, max_features=3, random_state=8017)
   
    rf_boston.fit(X_train, y_train)
    train_rf_scores.append(rf_boston.score(X_train, y_train))
    test_rf_scores.append(rf_boston.score(X_test, y_test))
    rf_boston._estimator_type='classifier'

plt.plot(test_rf_scores, 'bo-')
